// The @dma-retirement gap. The same array placed in an agent-shared region
// (dma_shared has a DMA agent) is plain `[u32;4]` -- placement is orthogonal to
// type today -- so the rvalue index-read that @dma rejects (see
// dma_index_read.bml) currently COMPILES. Retiring @dma naively would silently
// drop the read protection.
//
// The principled fix: derive Move/Dma from "placed in a region with a non-CPU
// agent" so this regains E326 without a hand-written adjective (usage dictates
// declaration). CHARACTERIZATION TEST -- when that lands, flip the assertion in
// test_region_agent_shared_index_read_currently_unprotected to expect E326.
var BUF: [u32; 4] @align(4) in dma_shared;
fn main() @context(thread) {
    BUF[0] = 1;
    var x: u32 = BUF[0];
    BUF[1] = x;
}
